  Reviewer 2 — The Soldier
 
  Competent, fair, structured. Acknowledges real strengths (practical
automation, DISL dataset, comprehensive evaluation), names real
weaknesses (limited baselines, low mitigation rate, false positive
risk), and asks for
  concrete, tractable additions (gas overhead table, failure taxonomy,
context abstraction details). No axe to grind. This is honest, mostly
correct, and not trying to champion or bury the paper — the
quintessential Soldier.

